        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Leipzig,</placeName>
                    <date>Jan. 26. 1871.</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>On page 128, note 45 of Vol. I. of your new work you quote some papers of Mr J. <hi rend="underline">Wood.</hi> But unfortunately you give only the references to the <hi rend="underline">Volumes</hi> without giving the <hi rend="underline">title</hi> of the periodical.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> May I ask you to write me, what periodical you mean? Perhaps I may find it out here, but I think the shortest way is to ask you directly. At any rate in a second edition you must give the title.</p>
<p>Two misprints: p. 118. note 28. Here the <hi rend="underline">second</hi> Volume of the “Variation” is meant. p. 20. note 23. Canestrini quotes <hi rend="underline">Hyrtl</hi> (the Vienna anatomist) instead of <hi rend="underline">Hyrt.</hi><ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Pray excuse my haste, and believe me | Yours ever truly, | J. Victor Carus</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Carus was preparing the German translation of <hi rend="italic">Descent.</hi> The title of the periodical in question, <hi rend="italic">Proceedings of the Royal Society of London</hi>, was added to the list of errata at the beginning of the second volume of the first printing, and to the text of the second printing of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref>. The reference is to John Wood (1825–91).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The first correction was not made, although it was added to the list of errata at the beginning of the second volume of the first printing; the second was made in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1967.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, p. 14 n. 28. The references are to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_815.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Giovanni Canestrini</ref> and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5976.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Josef Hyrtl</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
